columns.name: id
columns.description: The identifier for the Distribution.

columns.name: arn
columns.description: The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) for the distribution.

columns.name: status
columns.description: The current status of the Distribution.

columns.name: caller_reference
columns.description: A unique value that ensures that the request can't be replayed.

columns.name: comment
columns.description: The comment originally specified when this Distribution was created.

columns.name: default_root_object
columns.description: The object that you want CloudFront to request from your origin.

columns.name: domain_name
columns.description: The domain name that corresponds to the Distribution.

columns.name: enabled
columns.description: Whether the Distribution is enabled to accept user requests for content.

columns.name: e_tag
columns.description: The current version of the configuration.

columns.name: http_version
columns.description: Specify the maximum HTTP version that you want viewers to use to communicate with CloudFront. The default value for new web Distributions is http2. Viewers that don't support HTTP/2 will automatically use an earlier version.

columns.name: is_ipv6_enabled
columns.description: Whether CloudFront responds to IPv6 DNS requests with an IPv6 address for your Distribution.

columns.name: in_progress_invalidation_batches
columns.description: The number of invalidation batches currently in progress.

columns.name: last_modified_time
columns.description: The date and time the Distribution was last modified.

columns.name: price_class
columns.description: A complex type that contains information about price class for this streaming Distribution.

columns.name: web_acl_id
columns.description: The Web ACL Id (if any) associated with the distribution.

columns.name: active_trusted_key_groups
columns.description: CloudFront automatically adds this field to the response if youâ€™ve configured a cache behavior in this distribution to serve private content using key groups.

columns.name: active_trusted_signers
columns.description: A list of AWS accounts and the identifiers of active CloudFront key pairs in each account that CloudFront can use to verify the signatures of signed URLs and signed cookies.

columns.name: aliases
columns.description: A complex type that contains information about CNAMEs (alternate domain names),if any, for this distribution.

columns.name: alias_icp_recordals
columns.description: AWS services in China customers must file for an Internet Content Provider (ICP) recordal if they want to serve content publicly on an alternate domain name, also known as a CNAME, that they've added to CloudFront. AliasICPRecordal provides the ICP recordal status for CNAMEs associated with distributions.

columns.name: cache_behaviors
columns.description: The number of cache behaviors for this Distribution.

columns.name: custom_error_responses
columns.description: A complex type that contains zero or more CustomErrorResponses elements.

columns.name: default_cache_behavior
columns.description: A complex type that describes the default cache behavior if you don't specify a CacheBehavior element or if files don't match any of the values of PathPattern in CacheBehavior elements. You must create exactly one default cache behavior.

columns.name: logging
columns.description: A complex type that controls whether access logs are written for the distribution.

columns.name: origins
columns.description: A complex type that contains information about origins for this distribution.

columns.name: origin_groups
columns.description: A complex type that contains information about origin groups for this distribution.

columns.name: restrictions
columns.description: A complex type that identifies ways in which you want to restrict distribution of your content.

columns.name: tags_src
columns.description: A list of tags assigned to the Maintenance Window

columns.name: viewer_certificate
columns.description: A complex type that determines the distribution's SSL/TLS configuration for communicating with viewers.
